00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:39,914 --> 00:00:42,125
Because he is now
the new Chief Operations Officer

2
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:43,334
of Vertex Global Holdings.

3
00:00:43,418 --> 00:00:45,587
<i>The company of the Valtrovis.</i>

4
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:48,381
<i>Bro? Bro, is that really you?</i>

5
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:49,257
<i>My brother!</i>

6
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,509
<i>You look like a big shot now.</i>

7
00:00:51,593 --> 00:00:52,802
<i>Hello, Angelito.</i>

8
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:53,970
Chiara Valtrovi.

9
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,138
Mikoy is in danger.

10
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,182
<i>Someone wants to kill him.</i>

11
00:00:59,809 --> 00:01:02,729
Because now you're the one
in a complicated situation.

12
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:26,753
Hopefully next time, you'll knock, huh.

13
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:33,510
There's a reason why I needed
to come to your apartment secretly.

14
00:01:33,593 --> 00:01:35,094
So no one sees us meeting.

15
00:01:35,178 --> 00:01:38,056
Isn't there a lot
of CCTV in this building?

16
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:45,146
And we discovered
that there are many dead spots

17
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,815
in the CCTV coverage.

18
00:01:46,898 --> 00:01:49,317
Like at the fire exit
and service elevators.

19
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,407
What are you doing here?

20
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,327
You already know why I came here.

21
00:02:01,496 --> 00:02:04,541
Do you have any
new information to give us?

22
00:02:05,041 --> 00:02:07,210
Easy, I just started.

23
00:02:08,002 --> 00:02:11,005
I'm still studying
the company's operations.

24
00:02:12,549 --> 00:02:14,467
Look, I need more time to understand

25
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:17,095
how Vertex is used

26
00:02:17,178 --> 00:02:19,347
for the movement of illegal cargo.

27
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:23,268
I don't even know
what illegal cargo they're exporting.

28
00:02:23,351 --> 00:02:26,020
Also, can you leave now?

29
00:02:26,104 --> 00:02:28,690
Chiara might show up again later.

30
00:02:28,773 --> 00:02:30,316
We might get caught again.

31
00:02:31,025 --> 00:02:32,610
Don't worry.

32
00:02:32,694 --> 00:02:34,237
Sianong is monitoring them,

33
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,115
and according to his information,

34
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:39,701
they flew with Viktor to Hong Kong.

35
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:43,746
Do you have any idea
what they'll do in Hong Kong?

36
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,875
They went to Disneyland?

37
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:49,294
I don't know. Went shopping, maybe?

38
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:52,380
I was too busy earlier at the office.

39
00:02:53,047 --> 00:02:55,091
I'm sorry if I'm pressuring you.

40
00:02:56,134 --> 00:02:59,387
I just want to make sure
we didn't miss any details.

41
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:02,473
I know I already agreed with you.

42
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:06,853
I will stand by that.

43
00:03:07,812 --> 00:03:08,980
Me too.

44
00:03:09,772 --> 00:03:12,275
I also want to finish this
as soon as possible.

45
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,402
But for me,

46
00:03:14,485 --> 00:03:17,947
I haven't noticed anything
suspicious at the office.

47
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:19,908
For now, it seems…

48
00:03:19,991 --> 00:03:22,660
all their operations look legit.

49
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:27,957
We have a theory at the office
on how they move the cargo.

50
00:03:34,672 --> 00:03:36,716
Where the exports are packaged.

51
00:03:36,799 --> 00:03:38,009
<i>But our theory is</i>

52
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:40,511
<i>while the container vans</i>
<i>are on the way to the port,</i>

53
00:03:40,595 --> 00:03:44,474
<i>some of them take a re-route</i>
<i>to change the packages.</i>

54
00:03:44,557 --> 00:03:46,684
<i>They go to a secret location.</i>

55
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:51,773
<i>And in that secret location,</i>
<i>they ship the illegal cargo.</i>

56
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:04,160
Is that AI?

57
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:06,371
Well, the syndicate looks stupid.

58
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:08,164
It's Sianong's idea.

59
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,960
He's kind of obsessed now
with AI-generated videos.

60
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:14,337
And he made this
so you can better visualize

61
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:16,256
how the Moravianos operate.

62
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:17,215
Oh, really?

63
00:04:17,298 --> 00:04:20,343
You know, tell Sianong he's being stupid.

64
00:04:20,426 --> 00:04:21,844
What does he think of me?

65
00:04:21,928 --> 00:04:23,346
I don't have imagination?

66
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:25,682
You know, between the two of us,

67
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:27,267
he seems more clueless.

68
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,310
You know, I have a theory about him.

69
00:04:29,894 --> 00:04:31,312
No one will really love him.

70
00:04:31,396 --> 00:04:32,897
He'll grow old alone.

71
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:33,815
Do you know why?

72
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:35,984
Because I really don't see

73
00:04:36,067 --> 00:04:38,236
any good character traits in him
that would make someone love him.

74
00:04:38,903 --> 00:04:39,737
None at all.

75
00:04:43,574 --> 00:04:44,909
Be careful.

76
00:04:46,077 --> 00:04:47,537
Because he can see and hear you.

77
00:04:52,208 --> 00:04:53,126
How?

78
00:05:05,346 --> 00:05:06,389
You've got some nerve.

79
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:07,849
You're still sabotaging me.

80
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:09,225
Backstabber!

81
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:14,022
You put surveillance in my condo?

82
00:05:16,691 --> 00:05:18,276
We need to monitor you.

83
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:21,237
Because your apartment
is the most vulnerable spot.

84
00:05:21,904 --> 00:05:23,489
And very real. And…

85
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,909
the intelligence we got
from Agent Kian is actionable,

86
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,077
that someone wants to kill you.

87
00:05:28,161 --> 00:05:30,621
Couldn't you at least have told me?

88
00:05:30,705 --> 00:05:33,082
I've been walking around here
naked for days.

89
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,877
And then you set up these things?

90
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,503
You actually have cameras?

91
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,213
My God.

92
00:05:41,799 --> 00:05:43,092
Can't you look at me?

93
00:05:44,594 --> 00:05:45,636
You saw something?

94
00:06:17,376 --> 00:06:18,586
He's good.

95
00:06:19,087 --> 00:06:20,213
What are you doing?

96
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:30,139
<i>And you even made me</i>
<i>a scandal in your office?</i>

97
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:31,682
Wow!

98
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:32,642
Fine then!

99
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,977
Good thing I make you happy.

100
00:06:35,061 --> 00:06:37,563
Don't worry, I already talked to them.

101
00:06:37,647 --> 00:06:38,898
Gosh!

102
00:06:38,981 --> 00:06:39,816
"I talked to them."

103
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:43,111
I'm sure, you also enjoyed seeing me
look like a fool in that video.

104
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,739
Is that really how shallow you think I am?

105
00:06:52,745 --> 00:06:56,332
I understand the difficult situation
I put you in.

106
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,417
And I admire you.

107
00:06:59,001 --> 00:07:00,503
Because despite my blackmail attempts,

108
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:02,213
you still trusted me.

109
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:08,803
If you're really struggling

110
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:10,847
and you don't want to continue,

111
00:07:12,056 --> 00:07:13,808
you can walk away from this mission.

112
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:16,811
I won't stop you.

113
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,439
I'll let you leave.

114
00:07:21,899 --> 00:07:23,067
Really?

115
00:07:23,151 --> 00:07:24,735
Alex, what are you doing?

116
00:07:25,486 --> 00:07:27,196
Do you know what you're doing right now?

117
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:30,867
Why are you giving an exit option
to our only asset?

118
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,452
Let me make this clear.

119
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,413
You're saying it's okay with you

120
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:38,791
if I don't continue spying on them?

121
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:39,917
Against the Moravianos?

122
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:46,507
<i>Hello, Alex?</i>

123
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:49,385
Why are you giving an exit option
for Mr. Pinagpala?

124
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:54,307
<i>Are you out--</i>

125
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:56,476
Alex!

126
00:07:57,768 --> 00:07:58,811
Hello?

127
00:08:02,356 --> 00:08:04,442
I think your partner heard you.

128
00:08:04,525 --> 00:08:06,444
Between Sianong and me,

129
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:08,279
I'm the senior officer.

130
00:08:12,074 --> 00:08:13,075
Is this a trap?

131
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:15,953
Maybe later,

132
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:18,706
you'll suddenly lock up my brother.

133
00:08:22,710 --> 00:08:25,671
I'm just giving you the option
to not do this.

134
00:08:26,756 --> 00:08:27,840
And you're right.

135
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:30,426
We started on the wrong foot.

136
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:34,639
I blackmailed you,

137
00:08:34,722 --> 00:08:37,016
so you would agree to this position.

138
00:08:38,518 --> 00:08:40,561
And I don't think that was the right way.

139
00:08:41,312 --> 00:08:43,022
If I'm going to take down the Moravianos,

140
00:08:43,105 --> 00:08:44,941
I will do it the right way.

141
00:08:45,608 --> 00:08:47,818
And I won't force an innocent

142
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:49,737
and good person like you.

143
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:52,365
Think about it carefully, Mikoy.

144
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:55,993
Just continue this mission

145
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:59,580
if you want to do it,
and if it really comes from your heart.

146
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:08,130
Oh my goodness! It's Chiara!

147
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:09,882
If I leave,

148
00:09:10,424 --> 00:09:13,052
how will you build a case
against the Moravianos?

149
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,304
I'm sure I can find a way.

150
00:09:15,888 --> 00:09:17,473
But it won't be easy.

151
00:09:18,474 --> 00:09:21,018
But I won't give up on the Moravianos.

152
00:09:21,102 --> 00:09:23,854
And I won't stop until they're imprisoned

153
00:09:23,938 --> 00:09:25,189
because that's the right thing.

154
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,361
Alex!

155
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:31,821
Alex, answer…

156
00:09:32,989 --> 00:09:34,198
the phone!

157
00:09:50,089 --> 00:09:51,090
It's Chiara.

158
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:56,095
Hey!

159
00:10:02,643 --> 00:10:03,769
How are you?

160
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:06,439
You already missed me so much.

161
00:10:06,522 --> 00:10:08,024
Yes, of course.

162
00:10:08,107 --> 00:10:09,317
Come on.

163
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:13,946
What are you doing?

164
00:10:18,951 --> 00:10:20,620
What are you doing here?

165
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:23,080
I thought you were in Hong Kong?

166
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,418
Papa had a business meeting, and then,

167
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:30,004
I took that chance to go shopping.

168
00:10:30,087 --> 00:10:31,088
But we have to go home.

169
00:10:33,132 --> 00:10:36,636
Wait, how did you know we had
a quick getaway in Hong Kong?

170
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,643
I think you mentioned it to me.

171
00:10:43,726 --> 00:10:44,810
Or maybe your mom?

172
00:10:47,271 --> 00:10:48,731
Yes, maybe it was Mom.

173
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:51,442
She can't stop talking about you.

174
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:54,779
She really wanted you to join
the shopping trip, but I said,

175
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,739
"Mama, no.

176
00:10:56,822 --> 00:10:59,325
Because he's really busy with Vertex."

177
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:02,244
But she insisted, since
it's just a short visit, anyway.

178
00:11:02,995 --> 00:11:05,164
You know, you guys are intense, huh?

179
00:11:05,247 --> 00:11:07,583
Turning Hong Kong into Cubao.

180
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:09,335
Have you eaten?

181
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:11,712
Not yet.

182
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,672
I was going to cook, but…

183
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:16,175
-Well, let me cook something for you.
-Oh, no, no.

184
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,636
You know, let's just eat out.

185
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:19,970
My treat. Okay?

186
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:20,930
-No need.
-No.

187
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,223
-You'll just get more tired.
-Please.

188
00:11:22,306 --> 00:11:23,849
-No, I promise, I won't get tired.
-Forget it.

189
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:27,228
-I'll cook.
-No, no.

190
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:29,021
I seldom cook.

191
00:11:36,779 --> 00:11:38,364
Have you eaten already?

192
00:11:39,573 --> 00:11:41,492
It's nothing. It's just a mess.

193
00:12:22,908 --> 00:12:24,160
I told you so.

194
00:12:27,455 --> 00:12:28,414
Mikoy?

195
00:12:28,497 --> 00:12:29,707
Are you okay?

196
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:45,181
Sweetheart, just relax there.

197
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,515
I'm almost done.

198
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:48,434
Okay?

199
00:13:02,364 --> 00:13:04,909
Sweetheart, do you know
where my charger is?

200
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:07,745
-Maybe in the room?
-Oh, no.

201
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:13,167
Just keep cooking, okay?

202
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:21,926
-What happened?
-I don't know.

203
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:23,010
Maybe there's a fire.

204
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:25,262
Come on. Let's just go down.

205
00:13:25,804 --> 00:13:26,931
-Come on. Let's go.
-Look--

206
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:29,475
What are you doing?

207
00:13:29,558 --> 00:13:31,310
Why are you compromising our mission?

208
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:32,686
Look at what you've been doing.

209
00:13:32,770 --> 00:13:34,522
You almost put yourself in danger.

210
00:13:34,605 --> 00:13:36,607
I'm just doing what I think is right.

211
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:38,317
What you think is right?

212
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:41,862
Then why did you let our own asset leave?

213
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:44,823
I had to do that.

214
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:46,700
For Mikoy to be an effective asset,

215
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:48,410
he has to believe in our mission,

216
00:13:48,494 --> 00:13:51,247
and he has to do it willingly.

217
00:13:53,624 --> 00:13:54,458
May I remind you

218
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:58,337
how we set up Mikoy and his brother
so that he would I agree to this mission?

219
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:01,131
You think people will just willingly

220
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,633
do the right thing?

221
00:14:02,716 --> 00:14:05,886
Without threatening them?
Without giving them a warning?

222
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:10,849
Agent Alex, that's fake news!

223
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:15,646
Because the truth is,

224
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:19,441
most people will choose the easier option

225
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:21,026
rather than what's right.

226
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,538
Hello, Metro Manila.

227
00:15:37,853 --> 00:15:40,314
Dad? Mom?

228
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,191
Our son is handsome!

229
00:15:42,274 --> 00:15:43,525
Wow!

230
00:15:43,609 --> 00:15:45,235
Give me a hug, son!

231
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:48,989
You're so handsome.

232
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:55,704
Wait, what is this for?

233
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:57,456
Is it my birthday?

234
00:15:58,248 --> 00:15:59,583
Well…

235
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:02,211
I was really bothered
by how you looked last night.

236
00:16:02,294 --> 00:16:04,004
You looked really stressed.

237
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:06,840
So I called Mom and Dad for you.

238
00:16:07,341 --> 00:16:08,801
Actually, it worked out

239
00:16:08,884 --> 00:16:10,928
because we had a big order here in Manila.

240
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:12,554
And when we were told

241
00:16:13,847 --> 00:16:15,724
we'd ride on a private jet,

242
00:16:16,308 --> 00:16:19,311
of course, who are we, so naturally,

243
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,730
well, a private jet,
and we'll save money too.

244
00:16:21,814 --> 00:16:23,857
-Right?
-What?

245
00:16:23,941 --> 00:16:25,526
We have an order in Manila?

246
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:27,236
Nice!

247
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:30,781
Looks like our social media marketing
is working there, huh?

248
00:16:30,864 --> 00:16:31,991
Oh dear!

249
00:16:32,074 --> 00:16:35,744
The one who ordered is your friend.

250
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:40,124
-My friend?
-That's right.

251
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,291
Yes.

252
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:43,877
The name was Alex.

253
00:16:43,961 --> 00:16:45,796
They even asked me.

254
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:47,589
They said, "Where is he?"

255
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,633
I said, "He's here in Manila."

256
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:52,511
You're already here
because you got a new job

257
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:53,971
at Chiara's company.

258
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,682
Who's that friend of yours, sweetheart?

259
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:05,441
Actually, I can't really say
if it's a friend.

260
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:08,235
You know, it's like
we just know each other.

261
00:17:09,653 --> 00:17:11,238
How did you guys meet?

262
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,702
How did I even meet?
Actually, I don't even know.

263
00:17:16,785 --> 00:17:18,620
It's been a long time. I don't know.

264
00:17:18,704 --> 00:17:21,081
Dear, why don't you message,

265
00:17:21,165 --> 00:17:22,958
or why don't you message on Fishbook?

266
00:17:26,628 --> 00:17:27,463
That's right, too,

267
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:31,091
because it's important to have
someone you know here in Manila.

268
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:32,801
So that sometimes

269
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,970
you have company for drinks.

270
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:36,055
That's right.

271
00:17:36,138 --> 00:17:37,347
You know what?

272
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:40,434
We were worried about Chiara's message.

273
00:17:40,517 --> 00:17:43,854
Are you stressed out with your new job?

274
00:17:45,981 --> 00:17:47,733
Mom, I'm okay.

275
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:50,652
Of course, it's natural
to still adjust a little.

276
00:17:50,736 --> 00:17:52,154
It's a new job after all.

277
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:55,365
Even during my first months
as a waiter in Prague,

278
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:57,367
I was totally exhausted too.

279
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:59,661
But I'll get used to it.

280
00:18:00,162 --> 00:18:01,413
I can handle it, right?

281
00:18:02,206 --> 00:18:06,627
That's why I thought maybe it would help
if Mom and Dad were here for now.

282
00:18:06,710 --> 00:18:09,880
So you can reduce some of your stress.

283
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,674
What about Angelito?

284
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,802
He doesn't have classes today, right?

285
00:18:41,829 --> 00:18:44,373
What? You're so noisy!

286
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:46,583
If you don't want to sleep,
let others sleep!

287
00:18:47,417 --> 00:18:48,418
What the!

288
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,508
Who's this girl?

289
00:18:59,012 --> 00:19:00,180
Hello, son!

290
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:03,308
We're here with your brother.
Do you want to drop by?

291
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:04,726
You don't have class today, right?

292
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:06,979
Mom.

293
00:19:07,062 --> 00:19:09,481
I really need to finish something.

294
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,108
Why are you whispering?

295
00:19:12,609 --> 00:19:13,902
You're also whispering.

296
00:19:13,986 --> 00:19:15,028
No…

297
00:19:15,612 --> 00:19:17,072
Okay. Son!

298
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:19,283
We're just here.

299
00:19:19,366 --> 00:19:22,953
We brought your favorite
ube-flavored cake.

300
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:27,416
Okay.

301
00:19:27,916 --> 00:19:29,126
I'll come right away.

302
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:31,795
Wait, what are you busy with?

303
00:19:31,879 --> 00:19:34,756
Hopefully it's not just studying,
or your brain will turn into cake.

304
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:35,674
Yes, brother.

305
00:19:35,757 --> 00:19:37,759
I really need to finish something.

306
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:40,637
But I'll come there right away, okay?

307
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:45,684
<i>Why are you so noisy?</i>

308
00:19:54,693 --> 00:19:56,028
What was that?

309
00:19:56,111 --> 00:19:57,654
She said "babe"?

310
00:19:58,155 --> 00:19:59,406
Nice!

311
00:19:59,489 --> 00:20:02,951
Our baby Angelito is grown up!

312
00:20:05,662 --> 00:20:06,997
He said "babe".

313
00:20:11,793 --> 00:20:13,420
-You think that's funny?
-No class--

314
00:20:13,503 --> 00:20:14,463
There's no class!

315
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:16,965
Doing PE in the room!

316
00:20:17,049 --> 00:20:18,008
And also…

317
00:20:19,009 --> 00:20:20,010
Bro,

318
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:22,888
you need to come here.

319
00:20:22,971 --> 00:20:24,556
I need your help.

320
00:20:25,974 --> 00:20:28,393
I don't even know how
she got into my room.

321
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:30,854
Bro, do I look like someone
for an organic encounter?

322
00:20:34,441 --> 00:20:37,319
No, as far as I know, I was just sleeping,

323
00:20:38,070 --> 00:20:40,572
and when I woke up,
she was already beside me in bed.

324
00:20:42,449 --> 00:20:44,117
Seriously, I don't know!

325
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:47,329
Hey!

326
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:49,790
Do you have a toothbrush?

327
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:53,335
And also, can I borrow this?

328
00:21:17,109 --> 00:21:18,151
Oh.

329
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:22,572
Okay, sir.

330
00:21:27,661 --> 00:21:30,539
Is what I read in Sianong's report true?

331
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:32,165
You offered our asset,

332
00:21:32,249 --> 00:21:34,668
Mikoy, an option out?

333
00:21:36,295 --> 00:21:37,254
Yes, sir.

334
00:21:37,838 --> 00:21:38,672
And I'm sorry, sir,

335
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:41,049
if the decision seems
illogical or impulsive.

336
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,678
But when I talked to Mikoy,
I felt his struggle.

337
00:21:50,600 --> 00:21:52,060
But just know,

338
00:21:53,353 --> 00:21:55,188
without Mikoy,

339
00:21:56,440 --> 00:21:59,151
your work will become harder.

340
00:22:04,865 --> 00:22:06,074
You can count on me.

341
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:18,378
What now?

342
00:22:20,589 --> 00:22:22,716
You got scolded badly by the boss, right?

343
00:22:24,259 --> 00:22:26,762
He was really disappointed
with the decisions you made.

344
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:27,846
Imagine,

345
00:22:27,929 --> 00:22:32,559
that's our agency director,
and he was really mad at you.

346
00:22:37,022 --> 00:22:38,398
Totally, Bok.

347
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:43,153
Not only scolded, he almost exploded.

348
00:22:44,029 --> 00:22:46,073
I almost turned into a sponge.

349
00:22:53,497 --> 00:22:56,500
Mikoy is an important asset,
you know that.

350
00:22:56,583 --> 00:22:59,294
So we can't just let him leave.

351
00:23:04,174 --> 00:23:05,175
Bok.

352
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:12,057
The important thing now is to find out

353
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:13,934
when he will answer us.

354
00:23:14,017 --> 00:23:17,270
Whether he is willing
to fight for us or not.

355
00:23:26,696 --> 00:23:29,825
I don't want to wait and just rely
on Mikoy's decision.

356
00:23:32,410 --> 00:23:33,954
So?

357
00:23:34,037 --> 00:23:35,038
What's your plan?

358
00:23:38,959 --> 00:23:40,127
What do you mean?

359
00:23:51,138 --> 00:23:53,348
I think we need to focus our energy

360
00:23:53,431 --> 00:23:54,975
on Chiara Valtrovi.

361
00:23:56,935 --> 00:23:59,396
Because it's already
known in the whole town,

362
00:23:59,479 --> 00:24:00,564
it's about to explode!

363
00:24:00,647 --> 00:24:01,857
The name…

364
00:24:01,940 --> 00:24:03,066
Angelo!

365
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:05,944
<i>I have a strong feeling</i>
<i>that she knows something about all this.</i>

366
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:10,407
<i>And she is the key</i>
<i>to bringing down the Moravianos.</i>

367
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:11,449
Of course!

368
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:13,869
-The one and only.
-There, right there.

369
00:24:17,539 --> 00:24:19,416
Of course!

370
00:24:19,499 --> 00:24:21,293
You're something else!

371
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,837
Chiara, thank you so much.

372
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:26,339
You know, next time,
you don't need to do this.

373
00:24:27,174 --> 00:24:28,842
You went through all this trouble.

374
00:24:28,925 --> 00:24:30,886
It wasn't any trouble because,

375
00:24:30,969 --> 00:24:33,847
to be honest, I wasn't really doing much.

376
00:24:34,890 --> 00:24:36,183
You know, it's actually okay.

377
00:24:36,266 --> 00:24:39,311
Mom told me earlier that they
would stay with me first.

378
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,395
You?

379
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:42,397
Are you just staying here?

380
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,398
I mean,

381
00:24:43,481 --> 00:24:44,941
aren't you going to Prague anymore?

382
00:24:45,650 --> 00:24:47,944
Well, I already talked to Dad about it,

383
00:24:48,028 --> 00:24:50,697
and I might stay here for now.

384
00:24:50,780 --> 00:24:53,491
Maybe Mom and the others
will go back to Prague.

385
00:24:56,203 --> 00:24:57,370
Of course!

386
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:59,414
Could I say no?

387
00:24:59,497 --> 00:25:01,499
Of course, I want you to be here always.

388
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,753
So, if possible, don't leave anymore.

389
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:06,087
Please?

390
00:25:07,714 --> 00:25:09,883
All right, you still have a lot to do.

391
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:12,928
Bye!

392
00:25:13,011 --> 00:25:14,012
Okay.

393
00:25:17,265 --> 00:25:18,266
Bye.

394
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:40,080
I heard that you want to kill Mikoy.

395
00:25:57,013 --> 00:25:58,473
Are you sure?

396
00:26:02,978 --> 00:26:06,690
Are you sure you will never betray us?

397
00:26:09,484 --> 00:26:10,777
Have mercy.

398
00:26:11,278 --> 00:26:12,612
I have a family.

399
00:26:14,489 --> 00:26:17,284
I also have a family
that I need to protect.

400
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:20,745
The Valtrovi family.

401
00:26:21,371 --> 00:26:22,372
Have mercy.

402
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:32,215
I want to commit to this mission fully.

403
00:26:34,634 --> 00:26:37,554
I'm ready to help you
bring down the Moravianos.

404
00:26:37,637 --> 00:26:40,849
We both know what we need to protect him.

405
00:26:40,932 --> 00:26:43,518
<i>Because Mikoy is a good man.</i>
<i>And I don't want him to get involved</i>

406
00:26:43,601 --> 00:26:45,979
<i>with what we're doing here</i>
<i>in the Philippines.</i>

407
00:26:48,231 --> 00:26:50,817
Pinagpala, this is your end!

408
00:26:51,818 --> 00:26:53,236
-Agent Alex!
-Are you okay?

409
00:26:54,612 --> 00:26:56,406
Wait, stop tickling me!

410
00:26:57,949 --> 00:26:59,117
Gosh.

411
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,786
I hope you can make time for us.

412
00:27:01,870 --> 00:27:03,663
I promise, I'll make it up to you.

413
00:27:03,747 --> 00:27:06,750
How does Mr. Pinagpala make it up?

414
00:27:06,833 --> 00:27:08,001
MANILA ZOOLOGICAL &amp; BOTANICAL GARDEN

415
00:27:08,752 --> 00:27:10,795
<i>I know that you like him so much.</i>

416
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:14,257
<i>But will he accept who you are?</i>

